{
  "stem": "10905.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we took a ship called the a ship on the Polish registry going under the Belgian flag, and we came to the United States.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It took eight days to cross the Atlantic.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I thought I was on such a huge ship.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When we docked next to the we looked like a tugboat compared to her.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, it was a terribly, terribly small ship in comparison.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] It was a wonderful trip.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Food?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I hadn't had that much food and never plentiful food ever in my life, as I recalled.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We arrived to New York on a very steamy, muggy, horrible, typical New York summer day on July 16, 1947, and we arrived very early in the morning.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Coming from Switzerland, we did not have to go through-- I don't even know if Ellis Island was still operating then.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We did not have to go to Ellis Island.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The-- the people from the Department of Health came on board, immigration people came on board.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Took quite a while to get off.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the interesting thing was that I saw the West Side Highway and so many automobiles.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, you know, I was a seven-year-old kid.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in Europe, there were very, very few cars.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was very little fuel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the number of automobiles was just-- just mind-boggling.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it looked like cockroaches or mice coming down the West Side Highway in the early, early, early part of the morning.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And, of course, there was a terrible thunderstorm and rain, so it was overcast for a long time.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So even while the day had begun, not only at 6:00 or 7:00, but about 8, 9 o'clock in the morning, the height of rush hour, it was amazing.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
